# However, we still want to ignore the CONTENT of these directories if they are large, 
# but the instruction said "Boundary for sync-safe portable projects".
# Actually, if we want them to be "sync-safe", we usually IGNORE them in Git/Cloud sync.
# The user said: "If the vault is synced (e.g., via Dropbox/Git), these high-churn directories will cause sync conflicts and bloat."
# So they SHOULD be ignored. My previous replace was maybe wrong in intent if I use !.
# I will just update the paths to be relative to the new location.
artifacts/mlruns/
artifacts/runs/
artifacts/models/*.pkl
artifacts/models/*.bin
artifacts/.pytest_cache/
site/data/
site/reports/
node_modules/
.venv/
*.log
artifacts/
data/
mlruns/
